Decennial census population data

dec.Rd

These data sets contain population data for Kansas City, Missouri, sourced from the US Census Bureau's decennial census. Summary levels include city, county, census tract, census block group, census block, and ZIP code tabulation area (ZCTA).

Data sets were downloaded from data.census.gov using get_kc_pop(). See Guidance for Decennial Census of Population and Housing Data Users for information on how to use decennial census data.

Usage

dec_city_2010

dec_city_2020

dec_county_2010

dec_county_2020

dec_tract_2010

dec_tract_2020

dec_blockgroup_2010

dec_blockgroup_2020

dec_block_2010

dec_block_2020

dec_zcta_2010

dec_zcta_2020

Format

GEOID

  • Geographic identifier

  • Data type: character

NAME

  • Geographic area name

  • Data type: character

variable

  • Variable code

  • Data type: character

value

  • Population count

  • Data type: double

label

  • Descriptive variable label

  • Data type: character

concept

  • Census table name

  • Data type: character
